U.S. Geological Survey home page
About the USGS Denver Spectroscopy Lab

  http://speclab.cr.usgs.gov

   Personnel work on a variety of science research topics using methods
   including laboratory spectroscopy of terrestrial and planetary
   metarials, remote sensing spectroscopy of the Earth using imaging
   spectrometers, telescopes to study other planetary surfaces, and
   planetary probes with spectrometers and imaging spectrometers to study
   other planets. Scientific problems cover a wide range, from mineral
   exploration, environmental characterizations, global change, vegetation
   health, to planetary exploration throughout the solar system.

   Address and FAX numbers will be furnished upon request.
